# Dedicated build-context ignore for the backend image, which builds from the
# REPO ROOT (so it can COPY docs/workflow.schema.json — the normative schema the
# workflow linter loads at runtime). BuildKit uses this file for backend/Dockerfile
# and leaves the repo-root .dockerignore (used by the frontend image) untouched.
# Keep only backend/ + docs/; exclude everything else and the usual junk.
.git
.github
.claude
frontend
deploy
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info
**/.venv
**/venv
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
backend/tests
backend/Dockerfile
backend/Dockerfile.dockerignore
*.log
.env*
